      ]},
      { type: "p", text: `This is not a book of motivational slogans. It is a field manual for escaping the commodity trap.\nIf you are ready to stop competing purely on price and hard work, and ready to transition from being an invisible vendor to a highly recognized, premium brand in your category, you are in the right place .\nTurn the page. It is time to step off the factory floor and start building your strategic moat.` },
      { type: "quote", text: `Hard work scales the chaos; only strategy scales the profit` },
      { type: "h2", text: `[Table of Contents]` },
      { type: "p", text: `Preface\nIntroduction\nThe Invisible Problem\nPart 1: The Hard Work Trap\nChapter 1: The 18-Hour Founder\nWorksheet: Founder Dependence Check\nChapter 2: Why Good Manufacturing Businesses Plateau\nWorksheet: Growth Plateau Diagnosis\nPart 2: The Invisibility Problem\nChapter 3: The Peanut Butter Business\nWorksheet: Customer Spread Map\nChapter 4: The Commodity Trap\nWorksheet: Why Do Customers Really Choose Us?\nPart 3: What Brand Really Means in Manufacturing\nChapter 5: Brand Is Not Marketing\nWorksheet: Market Perception Exercise\nChapter 6: The Power of Strategic Focus\nPart 4: The Strategic Awakening\nChapter 7: The Real Growth Problem\nChapter 8: The Question Most Businesses Never Ask\nWorksheet: Where Might We Win?\nConclusion\nChapter 9: The Beginning of Strategy\nContinue the Journey\nStop Planning, Start Winning` },
      { type: "h1", text: `Preface` },
      { type: "p", text: `In my career, I haven’t just observed the engineering and manufacturing world from the sidelines—I have been in the trenches negotiating it.` },
      { type: "p", text: `During countless hours of Joint Venture discussions and facility visits with institutions like ISRO and IISc, I sat across the table from some of the brightest minds in the country. In those labs, I saw firsthand what absolute technical perfection looks like. I learned the rigorous discipline required to translate complex, cutting-edge science into real-world utility.` },
      { type: "p", text: `I took that same approach to the boardroom tables of industrial giants like L&T and GMR. Operating as a prospective JV partner, I learned exactly how the titans play the game. They don't just focus on bending metal or pouring concrete. They understand how to structure massive contracts, position themselves for absolute leverage, and drive revenue at scale. They understand that engineering is a tool, but strategy is the engine.` },
      { type: "p", text: `But when I stepped into the boardrooms of popular MSMEs across India for negotiations, I saw a completely different, tragic reality.` },
      { type: "p", text: `I would walk onto their factory floors and meet founders who possessed the deep tech understanding of a scientist. They were brilliant, driven men and women working 18-hour days to deliver flawless quality to their clients .` },
      { type: "p", text: `Yet, they were exhausted. Their revenue had flatlined, and their margins were being squeezed to death . Despite their incredible hard work, they lacked the commercial aggression and strategic architecture of the giants. Because of this, they were trapped—treated as invisible, replaceable vendors by the very corporations they were supplying .` },
      { type: "p", text: `That massive gap is why I stepped into strategy, and it is exactly why I wrote this book.\nMy mission is about fixing that exact disconnect. I help manufacturing founders combine their hard-earned engineering skills with the strategic leverage they need to protect their margins and command respect.` },
      { type: "p", text: `You already know how to make world-class products. You already know how to work hard. This book is designed to teach you how to structure your business so the market is finally forced to pay you what you are actually worth.\nIt is time to stop taking whatever orders fall into your lap. It is time to take absolute control of your market, your margins, and your future` }
