      { type: "h2", text: `Part 1: The Hard Work Trap` },
      { type: "p", text: `Illustration 1: The Founder Bottleneck (For Chapter 1)\nVisual: An hourglass or a funnel.\nDesign: At the top of the funnel, dozens of arrows are pouring in (labelled: Sales, Operations, HR, Purchasing, Quality). In the narrow, choked center of the hourglass is a single stick figure or icon labelled "The 18-Hour Founder." At the bottom, only a tiny trickle of progress is coming out.\nCaption: You cannot scale a business if every decision has to fit through one person’s brain.` },
      { type: "p", text: `Illustration 2: The Growth Plateau (For Chapter 2)\nVisual: A simple line graph. The X-axis is "Time" and the Y-axis is "Revenue."\nDesign: The line starts low, climbs aggressively like a steep staircase (labelled: Stage 2: Hustle & Growth), and then abruptly flattens out into a stubborn, horizontal, slightly bumpy line (labelled: Stage 3: The Efficiency Plateau).\nCaption: Hard work gets you up the stairs. Only strategy breaks through the ceiling.` },
      { type: "h2", text: `Part 2: The Invisibility Problem` },
